<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Meets Chilean Socialist Party Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, the Chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, in a meeting
today with Ricardo Lagos, leader of Chile's Socialist Party and
Party for Democracy, said that China and Chile have a very good
relationship and have many common views on international affairs.
</P>
<P>
He said that Lagos' visit will serve to further deepen
exchanges and cooperation between the two countries
</P>
<P>
Li visited Chile in November 1996, and he said that the NPC has
maintained friendly contacts with the Chilean parliament and many
parties like the Socialist Party and the Party for Democracy.
</P>
<P>
Maintaining bilateral exchanges and cooperation will help
promote friendly co-operative ties between the two countries in a
long-term and steady way, Li said. This will also play a positive
role in increasing mutual understanding and friendship between the
two peoples, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li also discussed the recent NPC session and the progress China
has made in its democracy and legal system.
</P>
<P>
Lagos said that his visit has helped him see in person Deng
Xiaoping's Theory and its practice in China and said he believes
that China will have even greater achievements under the new
leadership.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chilean government and people especially value
their cooperation with China and are ready to serve as a bridge
between the Pacific region and Latin American nations.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean government and people are highly interested in
China's progress and are also impressed very much by the
development goals and plans of the recent People's Congress, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Various parties in the Chilean parliament are taking an active
attitude toward Sino-chilean relations, he said, and his two
parties are willing to make their own effort.
</P>
<P>
Lagos is here as guest of the International Department of the
CPC Central Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
