<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Europe Strives for Close Ties With Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 22 (Xinhua) -- European Parliament President Jose
Maria Gil-Robles said here Wednesday the European Union would make
efforts to develop close ties and expand exchanges with Russia.
</P>
<P>
Gil-Robles, addressing Russia's lower house, the State Duma,
said that economic and political stability in Russia was important
for ensuring peaceful co-existence among nations world-wide.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that integration into the global economy was crucial
for Russia, Gil-Robles voiced his support for Moscow's bid to join
the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
Russia has been striving for admission to the WTO, the body
which acts as a monitor on goods and services trading in the world.
</P>
<P>
Gil-Robles, expressing full understanding of Russia's concern
about the expansion of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO), said the two sides should not be hostile to each other.
</P>
<P>
Russia and NATO have been at odds over the group's enlargement
into eastern Europe, a move Russia has said poses a threat to
Russia's national interest.
</P>
<P>
Gil-Robles, who arrived here Monday for a visit, held separate
talks with Russia's parliamentary leaders on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
