<HEADLINE> U.S. to Send Humanitarian Charters to Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The United States has
decided to send three humanitarian charters to Iraq by the end of
of this month, a U.N. source said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The source said the U.S. mission to the United Nations had
applied for permission from the United Nations Sanctions Committee
on Iraq this morning, which is expected to be approved by the
Committee very soon.
</P>
<P>
The source also said the initiative was sponsored by an
American non-governmental organization called AmeriCare and
supported by the Government of the United States, and the three
charters, via Oman, will arrive in Iraq on April 27, 28 and 29
respectively. The humanitarian supplies include medicine and
medical equipments.
</P>
<P>
The United States has been opposing any humanitarian planes to
Iraq. Its move at the present is a departure from its traditional
position of the past. The purpose of the move is unknown to the
international community.  
</P>
</TEXT>
