<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Commission Establishes European Study Centers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
executive arm of the European Union (EU), said on Wednesday it has
set up 25 study centers for issues concerning European integration.
</P>
<P>
The centers are scattered in universities of the 15 EU member
states where 54 new courses on European integration will be
taught. They will focus on the study of 202 projects, ranging from
community law and economic and political integration to the
history of the integration process.
</P>
<P>
The study centers, to be known as the Jean Monnet European
Centers of Excellence, are founded to bring greater visibility to
the universities' scientific and human resources on European
issues.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to contribute towards the development of
multi-disciplinary teaching, research and training activities and
the publication of directories on European teaching activities
within universities.
</P>
<P>
They are also expected to link the EU with the outside world at
local and regional levels by promoting various types of
cooperation initiatives.
</P>
<P>
A network is in operation with a teaching faculty specializing
in such projects as the European position in the framework of the
World Trade Organization, the union's Agenda 2000, the necessary
institutional reforms and the enlargement of the EU. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
