<HEADLINE> LIFFE Announces New Strategic Focus In Governance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Board of the London
International Financial Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE)
Wednesday proposed substantial changes to LIFFE's strategic focus
as well as to its trading platforms and corporate governance.
</P>
<P>
The Board is also reviewing how access rights to the Exchange
should be obtained and whether its shareholding structure should
be simplified.
</P>
<P>
The proposals will be published in the week beginning May 4,
according to an announcement by LIFFE.
</P>
<P>
The changes are designed to ensure that LIFFE has the
competitive strengths and the decision-making machinery necessary
to meet the rapidly changing needs of market users in the years
ahead.
</P>
<P>
LIFFE considers that the Company should adopt a profit
objective with the intention of increasing value for its
shareholders.
</P>
<P>
It further believes that LIFFE should remove impediments to
third party shareholders, but expects to remain predominantly
owned by the existing customers of the market.
</P>
<P>
The Company has commissioned further analysis to determine
whether these changes should entail the simplification of the
shareholding structure and the separation of shares and permits to
trade on the floor of the Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Jack Wigglesworth, Chairman of LIFFE, said: "The proposals are
not expected to alter materially the existing ownership of LIFFE."
</P>
<P>
However, "We need a new strategy, embracing new technology,
with a new focus, to meet the new needs of market users," he
added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
