abductors," said Boni.
</P>
<P>
South African pilot Robbie Burt, eight workers of the
International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) and Red Crescent
Societies, and a Kenyan pilot were captured after their aircraft
landed at an airstrip in north Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Boni said the Daud sub-clan controls the area where the group
were taken captive.
</P>
<P>
Efforts by the ICRC to secure the release of the ten people
continued on Wednesday. It still had no direct contact with the
kidnappers, and was negotiating through clan elders.
</P>
<P>
"The feeling is that these talks should be approached with
patience and circumspection," Boni said. 
