<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Kuwaiti Speaker of the
National Assembly Ahmed Abdul Al-Sadoun Wednesday urged the Iraqi
government to release its citizens jailed in Iraqi prisons,
Lebanese official National News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
After talks with his Lebanese counterpart Nabih Berri,
Al-Sadoun told reporters that the issue over prisoners has been
concerning Kuwait since it was liberated from Iraqi occupation
seven years ago.
</P>
<P>
In 1990, Iraq invaded its neighbor Kuwait and was forced to
leave it following the Gulf War led by the United States in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sadoun accused Iraq of using prisoners as "bargaining chips"
politically in dealing with Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
He said that at first Iraq denied that it detained Kuwaiti
citizens and then admitted it under the international pressure.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Arab countries would exert pressure
on the Iraqi government and urge it to cooperate with Kuwait
on this humanitarian issue.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sadoun arrived here on Wednesday morning from
Damascus. During his two-day visit, he will also hold talks with
Lebanese President Elias Hrawi and Prime Minister Rafik Hariri on
bilateral ties and regional affairs. 
</P>
