<HEADLINE> Russia, Italy Sign Military Cooperation Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Russian Defense Minister Igor
Sergeyev and visiting Italian counterpart Beniamino Andreatta
Wednesday signed a plan of military cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency reported, Andreatta expressed hope
that the plan would help "raise military cooperation between the
two countries to the level of political dialogue between Rome and
Moscow."
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, Italian officers will be able to receive
instruction at the Academy of the General Staff of the Russian
Federation, and Russian officers at Italian institutes, according
to the Italian minister.
</P>
<P>
The minister said he and Sergeyev agreed to hold a meeting of
the Russian and Italian chiefs of the general staff within the
year.
</P>
<P>
On the crisis in Kosovo where the ethnic Albanian majority is
rebelling against the Belgrade government, Andreatta said, "The
problem may put the existing equilibrium in the Balkans in
question."
</P>
<P>
Before the signing ceremony, the two side held talks on the two
countries' relations. Both ministers were satisfied with the
"perfectly" developed Russian-Italian relations.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta arrived in Moscow on Tuesday for a four-day official
visit.  
</P>
