<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-22 19:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Marks Holocaust Remembrance Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of people gathered
Wednesady night at Yad Vashem here for ceremonies marking the
Holocaust Martyrs' and Heroes' Remembrance Day.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony took place at Warsaw Ghetto Square in
front of Yad Washem, which is the Holocaust Memorial Hall
situated on Mount Herzl, with the participation of President Ezer
Weizman, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, local dignitaries and
envoys of foreign countries based in Israel.
</P>
<P>
The holocaust occurred during World War II, in which 6
million Jews were killed by Nazis and their collaborators,
leaving bitter memories for the Jews, the holocaust survivors and
the people of the whole world.
</P>
<P>
Yad Vashem was in a particular profound grief atmosphere
Wednesday night. Many holocaust survivors coming from Israel and
other parts of the world wept while commemorating their family
members and colleagues who were killed during the holocaust.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the ceremony, Weizman said this year Israel will
celebrate its 50 anniversary of independence, but Israel will not
forget those who had been killed during the holocaust.
</P>
<P>
"Israel can proclaim to the whole world that holocaust will be
never allowed to happen again and the memories of the 6 million
Jews will last forever," Weizman declared.
</P>
<P>
He said that Israel will further strengthen its friendly
relations with the countries with which Israel has had diplomatic
ties and will try its best to improve the relations with the
countries which do not have diplomatic relations with Israel,
particularly with the neighboring states.
</P>
<P>
"Israel has had friendly relations with Egypt and Jordan and I
hope Israel will speed up its peace negotiations with Syria,
Lebanon and Palestine," Weizman said.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu and representatives of the holocaust survivors also
spoke at the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
As part of the ceremony, six holocaust survivors, including
professors Yitzhak Gutman and Elazar Shafrir, kindled the
memorial flames.
</P>
<P>
Ceremonies for the holocaust remembrance day will continue on
Thursday. Sirens throughout Israel will sound at 10:00 a.m. local
time Thursday, when the country will stand for two minutes in
silent tribute to the memory of the 6 million Jewish
martyrs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
