details of the proposed plans and the setting up of weather, water
and environment watch stations around the Caspian Sea as well as
the creation of warning stations to alert people to imminent
floods, hailstones and storms.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the five littoral states, namely, Russia,
Turkmenistan, Kazakhstan, Azerbaijan and Iran attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Among the participants were also representatives from world
agencies like United Nations Development Program, World
Meteorological Organization, United Nations Educational,
Scientific and Cultural Organization and 18 other related agencies.
</P>
<P>
The ACCCSWWE was established in 1994 by the littoral states. The
first assembly was held in Bandar Anzali of Iran and the second
in Baku of Azerbaijan. 
