island of Bougainville of Papua New Guinea to cooperate in
promoting reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
In a presidential statement adopted here on Wednesday, the
Council expressed its strong support for the agreement while
welcoming a permanent cease-fire to take effect on April 30.
</P>
<P>
The peace accord ended nearly ten years of fighting between
secessionist forces and the PNG government for control of
copper-rich island of Bougainville.
</P>
<P>
The truce stipulated in the pact signed at Lincoln University
of New Zealand is being monitored by New Zealand, Australia, Fiji
and Vanuatu and a formal peace agreement for a permanent
cease-fire will be signed on the island on April 30.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council said it requested U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan to consider the composition and financial modalities of
U.N. involvement in the matter as the agreement called on the
U.N. "to play a role" in Bougainville.
</P>
<P>
A four-person U.N. survey team is leaving for PNG today to
assess the situation there. 
