some of them reportedly called on relevant authorities to expel
the parliamentarian from the Majlis.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the pro-government newspaper Salam on Wednesday
denied a rumor that Deputy Oil Minister Ali Hashemi, Rafsanjani's
son, has been arrested for corruption.
</P>
<P>
Rival factions run into a hot political fighting after
Karbaschi was detained on April 4 by the conservative judiciary on
corruption charges, which were rejected by the moderates as
politically motivated in an aim to weaken the government of
President Mohammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
Karbaschi was released a week ago following a direct
intervention by Rafsanjani and the supreme leader Ayatollah Ali
Khamenei. However, political fighting is still continuing in the
country as the conservatives still insist on public trial on the
major, a major supporter of Khatami. 
