<HEADLINE> Motor Accident Kills Mayor Supporters in Kampala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A motor accident killed seven
people and injured 24 others this evening as they were
celebrating the victory of Kampala's mayor-elect Nasser
Sebaggala.
</P>
<P>
Police said the lorry was running along a road when it lost
control and crashed into a crowd of the mayor-elect's supporters.
Investigations into the accident are still under way.
</P>
<P>
After the accident, other supporters set the lorry ablaze, but
the fire was soon extinguished by fire fighters.
</P>
<P>
Police authorities advised the people to seek police
permission before carrying out any celebrations so that they can
be given proper protection.
</P>
<P>
Since the announcement of Sebaggala's victory in the elections
held in the capital city, there have been a series of frenzied
road and street celebrations marking his success. 
