<HEADLINE> Museveni Re-Affirms Commitment to Attracting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni has re-affirmed his government's commitment of
supporting investors in the country.
</P>
<P>
The president made the pledge at a manufacturer association's
anniversary celebrations Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the function taking place at the association's show ground
near Kampala, Museveni expressed his government's readiness to
enter into investment ventures with private firms who are ready
to invest in the processing sector.
</P>
<P>
He said although there are some factories engaged in primary
products processing, the country will benefit more if the primary
products could be further processed to final products.
</P>
<P>
To encourage investment in the country, he added, the Uganda
Electricity Board has been urged to reduce electricity costs.
</P>
<P>
The president also said that the manufacturers' association
will continue to pursue policies favorable to investment such as
a liberalized economy, a deregulated marketing system as well as
providing security for investors.  
</P>
