<HEADLINE> Dolly, The Cloned Sheep, Becomes A Mother </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Dolly the sheep, the world's first
clone of an adult mammal, has made history again to become a
mother, its creator, Scotland's Roslin Institute, said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The institute said that Dolly gave birth to its first offspring
on April 13. The female lamb was named Bonnie and weighed 2.7
kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Dolly shocked the world a year ago when Roslin scientists
announced that it had been created from a single cell of an adult
ewe's udder.
</P>
<P>
Dolly's arrival has created worldwide fears about human
cloning, since it is the first time that an animal was cloned from
the cells of an adult mammal, which raises the prospect that the
same technique may be one day applied to humans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
