<DOCNO> XIE19980423.0067 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Jobless Claims Pick Up Last Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The number of Americans filing
first-time claims for unemployment benefits went up to an
eight-week high last week, the Labor Department reported here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment claims increased by 29,000 to a seasonally
adjusted 317,000 last week after having declined 24,000 to a
nine-month low of 288,000 the week before. The increase was the
largest since early August.
</P>
<P>
However, analysts believed some applicants probably delayed
filing claims as a result of the Spring holidays. And even with
the big growth, claims remained at a level signaling a healthy
labor market.
</P>
<P>
A four-week moving average of benefit claims went up to 306,750
last week from 306,000 the week before. The average has remained
in a narrow range between 303,000 and 312,000 for the past 11
weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
