<HEADLINE> Marine Tank Terminal Goes Operational In Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Dalian Marine Tank Terminal
Co. Ltd. began operations today in Dalian, a port city in China's
Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The enterprise was started by the Dalian Harbor Affairs Bureau
and Norway's Odfjell ASA, Japan's Mitsui, and the Netherlands' Van
Ommeron.
</P>
<P>
The 200,000-sq.m. terminal will cost 140 million US dollars and
is the city's first transportation infrastructure project to be
built with foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
It will have a 220,000-cu.m. capacity and an annual transport
capacity of 1.2 million tons of chemical products.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the construction cost 29.5 million US
dollars and was completed in 22 months by Chinese and foreign
construction workers and provided a 60,000-cu.m. capacity and a
transport capacity of 400,000 tons annually.
</P>
<P>
The terminal is equipped with a state-of-the-art computer
system. 
</P>
