<HEADLINE> Education and Discipline Stressed For Law Enforement Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Luo Gan, the secretary of the
Central Political Science and Law Committee, called for greater
effort to be made in educating and disciplining people working in
judicial and law enforcement departments.
</P>
<P>
At a televised phone meeting today, Luo said although the
majority of people working in judicial and public security
departments are good, a few have been corrupt or have broken the
law in one way or another, seriously damaging the prestige and
image of the whole team, the Party, and the government.
</P>
<P>
He said the education and rectification work should begin with
self-examination and study of regulations on corruption.
</P>
<P>
The Central Political Science and Law Committee already clearly
prohibits bribes, refusing to help people asking for help, beating
and cursing people, getting involved in the entertainment
business, and offering protection for illegal businesses among
political and law department staff members.
</P>
<P>
Luo stressed that violations of laws and regulations by
judicial and law enforcement workers must be thoroughly
investigated and punished, and the public must be given a clear
explanation about the cases.
</P>
<P>
Those who are not qualified must be retrained or dismissed
while the concerned departments must not cover up or provide
shelter for the law breakers, Luo said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
