<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WB to Raise 25m Dollars to Boost Pak Fruit Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank will create a
Private Sector Development Fund with an initial amount of 25
million U.S. dollars to boost Pakistan's export of fruits,
vegetables and horticulture.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed Thursday by Consultant of the World Bank
A.R. Siddiqui while talking to members of the Karachi Chambers of
Commerce and Industry in the southern port city, according to the
Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
A research study under the Agricultural Sector Investment
Project had been prepared which will be submitted to the World
Bank soon suggesting ways and means to prevent post-harvest losses
of fruits and vegetables, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that about 25 to 30 percent of fruits, vegetables and
horticulture are being wasted due to improper plucking and absence
of road network in the cultivation area.
</P>
<P>
The fund will be provided to the private sector and the World
Bank will also find out foreign companies to set up joint ventures
in Pakistan for processing of fruits and vegetables, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
