<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Former Brazilian star Jose Clayton
was picked up to the training camp on Thursday by Tunisian head
coach Henri Kasperczak for the World Cup finals this summer in
France.
</P>
<P>
The inclusion of Clayton, a defender with quality and skills,
will surely intensify the Tunisian backcourt during its World Cup
outing, according to Kasperczak who announced the 22-member
interim roster which also included league top scorer Belhassen.
</P>
<P>
Clayton was eligible for the national squad after he was
granted the Tunisian citizenship recently following his three-year
professional career in the African country.
</P>
<P>
The roster did not include those Tunisians who currently played
for clubs in Europe, but they remained as candidates for the
Tunisian national squad as the final roster will be fixed only
after the series of training, said Kasperczak.
</P>
<P>
To tune up for the World Cup finals, Kasperczak has inked an
intensive program to be in effect from April 27 for six
international friendlys, and those players in overseas clubs will
be called back under schedule.
</P>
<P>
The Tunisian team will play first against Georgia at home on
May 2 before flying to Europe for a three-week training and four
warm-ups.
</P>
<P>
In Europe, They are scheduled to play Vicenza of Italy on May
21, a French local club three days later, Vienna of Austria on May
27, and the Chilean nationals on May 30.
</P>
<P>
The Tunisian footballers will back home on June 4 to play their
last opponents of Wales two days later before boarding on their
World Cup flight to France on June 9. 
</P>
