<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Grateful Japanese Friend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao Thursday met with Kazushige Hozumi, a Japanese citizen
whose life was saved by the Chinese people 14 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Hozumi, who visited China in 1984 at the invitation of the
Chinese government under a youth exchange program, suffered
gastric bleeding and went into a coma in Nanjing, a city in east
China.
</P>
<P>
Because the bleeding was very severe, Hozumi's life was
seriously endangered. He needed an immediate operation.
</P>
<P>
Hu, then first secretary of the Central Committee of the
Chinese Communist Youth League, organized a successful operation
in the absence of Hozumi's relatives.
</P>
<P>
Hu has been concerned about Hozumi's health since the operation
and asked the Chinese Embassy to arrange a meeting with Hozumi
during his visit to Japan.
</P>
<P>
Hozumi, who is now in good health, said he was very happy to
meet Hu and expressed his thanks to the Chinese vice-president and
the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Hozumi has devoted himself to the promotion of Sino-Japanese
friendship since he returned to Japan. He told Hu that he would
continue to dedicate himself to Sino-Japanese friendly ties to
express his gratitude to the Chinese people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
