<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Promotion of Tehran-Tokyo Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Vice Speaker Hassan Rowhani of the
Iranian Majlis (Parliament) Thursday called for promoting
Tehran-Tokyo ties in political, economic and cultural fields,
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with visiting Japanese Deputy Foreign Minister
Masahiko Komura, Rowhani said that Iran's foreign policy is based
on the principle of removing obstacles to its relations with other
countries, citing Iranian-European relations as "the best
example."
</P>
<P>
Iran and the European Union (EU) warmed up their relations
after reaching a compromise last November over a verdict of a
Berlin court accusing Tehran of killing four Iranian Kurdish rebel
leaders in Germany.
</P>
<P>
Rowhani noted that the establishment of parliamentary
friendship groups would help promote Tehran-Tokyo relations in
all fields, particularly in parliamentary affairs.
</P>
<P>
He assured the Japanese official that Iran has no intention to
seek weapons of mass destruction and is willing to see the entire
region free from such weapons.
</P>
<P>
Rowhani expressed hope that the regional countries would
pressure Israel into destroying such kind of weapons.
</P>
<P>
Komura voiced satisfaction with the "friendly relations"
between Japan and Iran, saying that Tokyo is willing to open a new
chapter in the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Referring to dialogs among different civilizations proposed by
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami, he said the Japanese
government regards the proposal as "very positive for the entire
region and the whole world."
</P>
<P>
The Japanese official arrived here on Wednesday for a four-day
visit, during which he is to deliver a message from Japanese Prime
Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto to Khatami. 
</P>
</TEXT>
