<HEADLINE> Chinese, Portuguese Ministers Emphasize Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- China's State Development
Planning Commission Minister Zeng Peiyan, in a meeting with
Portuguese Minister of Economics Joaquim Pina Moura here today,
said that investment by both countries has already begun and China
would like to know more about Portugal economy and its investment
policy to explore possibilities for further cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China's overseas investment is still in a primary stage, Zeng
said, and mainly focuses on resources that are in short supply in
China, and if conditions permit, China will consider investing in
Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral economic and trade co-operation is expected to expand
after Macao's return in 1999, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moura said that China and Portugal can increase their
cooperation in investment and trade, and Macao can serve as a link
between the two.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese government supports China's early entry to the
World Trade Organization, he said, and believes that this is
helpful for the world trade balance.
</P>
<P>
Moura is here in the company of Portugal's Prime Minister
Antonio Guterres.  
