<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and Burkina Faso
signed two agreements here Thursday to expand and strengthen
trade, economic and industrial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed at a meeting here attended by
Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad and visiting Burkina
Faso President Blaise Compaore.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia will send a business delegation to the African country
to seek joint-venture opportunities. There was a lot of potential
for cooperation, Mahathir said..
</P>
