<HEADLINE> Bomb Explosions Cause Fire in Athens Jewish Council Offices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Two bombs exploded Thursday in a
building housing the offices of the Jewish Council in downtown
Athens, capital of Greece, causing small fires but no injuries.
</P>
<P>
The two makeshift bombs, consisting of gas cannisters, were
placed on the stairs between the fifth and sixth floors of the
building and in the elevator respectively, police said.
</P>
<P>
