<HEADLINE> Int'l Medical Insurance Provider Expands Market in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A Britain-based international
medical insurance provider said here Thursday that there is a
strong business potential in Asia despite the recent financial
turmoil in this region.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to leading Hong Kong insurance brokers and the media
at a reception to celebrate the establishment of the Hong Kong
office of the Goodhealth Worldwide, Martin Garcia, director of the
 Hong Kong office, said that increasing corporate and consumer
awareness in Asia of the value of worldwide medical insurance
cover is creating opportunities for insurers.
</P>
<P>
Goodhealth Worldwide Ltd. based in Sussex, England, was created
 in January 1995 to provide tailored medical insurance services
catering to the specialized needs of people living, working or
traveling outside their normal country of residence.
</P>
<P>
In January 1998, Goodhealth opened an office in Hong Kong as
the company's headquarters in the Asia-Pacific region to provide
comprehensive medical insurance services for this region.
</P>
<P>
Garcia said that Asia is home to many expatriates, as well as
an increasing number of Asian professionals who are traveling,
living and working outside of their home bases.
</P>
<P>
These individuals require policies that provide comprehensive
benefits not just at home, but around the world, Carcia said.
</P>
<P>
International healthcare cover is a necessity for those who
travel frequently, if one is to avoid astronomical hospital bills,
 or the risk of being refused treatment altogether.
</P>
<P>
Goodhealth is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Europea Insurance
Management Holdings (IMH) Ltd., a Britain-based insurance broking
firm.
</P>
<P>
At the same reception, Chris Farley-West, Chairman of Europea
IMH Ltd., noted that as the business and financial center of
Asia, Hong Kong makes an excellent base for Goodhealth's
operations in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
He said that Goodhealth's Falcon Health Plan offers refund of
medical costs, including in-patient, out-patient, evacuation,
drugs, dressings, and nursing fees, of up to 500,000 pounds (about
 825,000 U.S. dollars) every year. Options include cover for
dental and pregnancy costs.
</P>
<P>
Falcon Plan policyholders can opt to receive treatment in any
country of their choice, even for non-emergency elective
procedures. A 24-hour, multilingual help line is available for
maximum peace of mind.
</P>
<P>
Goodhealth's Falcon Plan is currently available through agents
in Hong Kong, China's mainland, Singapore, Japan, Malaysia,
Indonesia, Vietnam, Thailand, Nepal and Brunei. 
</P>
</TEXT>
