<HEADLINE> Mongolia Elects New Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia's Great Hural (the
parliament) Thursday elected Tsakhya Elbegdorj as the country's
new prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The parliament's Information Section told Xinhua that
Elbegdorj, vice chairman of the Great Hural, was elected with 61
votes for and six against.
</P>
<P>
The vote was called after the entire cabinet, led by the then
prime minister, Mendsaikhan Enkhsaikhan, offered to
resign. President Nachagynon Bagabandy on Monday agreed to the en
masse resignation.
</P>
<P>
The Great Hural approved the resignation on Tuesday with 59
votes for and one against.
</P>
<P>
Elbegdorj, a 35-year-old former journalist, has until next
Tuesday to appoint a new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
In an address to the national television Wednesday evening,
Elbegdorj said his new government will endeavor to maintain the
continuity of the nation's opening-up foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
Elbegdorj was elected president of the National Democratic
Party (NDP) in April, 1996. The NDP is the largest party in the
ruling Democratic Union Coalition, which came to power in
1996. 
</P>
