<HEADLINE> Beijing Guo'an Wins Delayed Match in Chinese League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Guo'an exploited its home
advantage to beat Shandong Luneng 3-1 in a delayed match of the
Chinese first division soccer league here Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
After the victory, Guo'an climbed to the fourth place in the
14-team league on nine points, just one point shy of third-placer
Qingdao Hainiu as Guo'an still played one less match due to its
early outing in the Asian Cup Winners' Cup tournament wherein it
finished third.
</P>
<P>
Against strong winds after the morning rain, the Guo'an eleven
enjoyed apparent advantage in the pitch with the free kicks on the
brink of the penalty box in particular.
</P>
<P>
With 19 minutes into the game, Nan Fang sneaked through two
defenders to slam home the opener from a header off Spanish import
Olivas Rubio Andres who jumped high enough to connect a right-wing
free kick.
</P>
<P>
Nine minutes later, the Spaniard dived in the box but failed to
find the target as his header flew inches off the right post.
</P>
<P>
Within a minute after the break, the visiting squad awarded an
owl goal to the home side in a goal-mouth scramble.
</P>
<P>
From a perfect pass off Andres, Li Hongzheng found the ball
first with his right foot which bounced back from the post before
it went into the net off the body of a Luneng defender.
</P>
<P>
After it failed to convert any of the five corner kicks into
goal in the first half, Luneng resorted to the tactics of counter
attack after the break.
</P>
<P>
In the 54th minute, Song Yumin was found unspotted in a swift
counter attack but his close-range low shot was blocked by Guo'an
goalie Yao Jian.
</P>
<P>
Nine minutes later, Xing Rui eventually scored for Luneng from
a free kick in front of the penalty box which flew over the wall
of defenders and sneaked into the net just below the bar.
</P>
<P>
In the 77th minute, Wang Shaolei dampened any hope of Luneng
for a win, netting in an instant free kick before the defenders
even positioned themselves on time. 
</P>
