Lagos, leader of Chile's Socialist Party and Party for Democracy.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the Chinese Communist Party,
said that China values its relationships with Latin American
countries and pointed to the comparatively long history of
political, economic and cultural contacts.
</P>
<P>
"China hopes to increase political dialog with all countries
in Latin America in order to promote understanding and trust,
bolster cultural exchanges and economic cooperation, and develop a
friendly and cooperative relationship based on long-term
stability, equality and mutual benefit," said Jiang.
</P>
