<HEADLINE> Multimedia Market Displays Vast Potential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- China has yet to tap the vast
potential of huge multimedia market.
</P>
<P>
The Multimedia '98 Exhibition opened today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The ongoing Fourth International Exhibition on Multimedia
Technology and Applications, the largest of its kind ever held in
China, has attracted more than 150 domestic and overseas companies.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition shows the progress of China's multimedia
industry, including Chinese software which has won international
prizes and creative multimedia tools developed domestically.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the sponsoring State Economic and Trade
Commission pointed to the rapid growth of China's multimedia
market since the introduction of related technology in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Multimedia has emerged as a common component for China's
personal computers.
</P>
<P>
China is expected to surpass Japan and become the world's
second largest PC market within the next few years.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has placed priority on the development
of a series of multimedia projects, including technology,
platforms, applications and multimedia environments.
</P>
<P>
Relevant officials note that China has not as yet reached an
accelerated pace in developing its own multimedia technology and
products.
</P>
<P>
However, most major international multimedia companies have
entered the Chinese market as evidenced by the number on
multinationals participating in the exhibition, including IBM, DEC
and Microsoft.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, which will run through Monday, will feature
forums on the development strategy for China's multimedia market
and relevant technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
