<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Hospitals Set to Adopt New Symbol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- China's hospitals, clinics and
applicable medical institutions are preparing to adopt a white
cross superimposed on a clover leaf design composed of four red
hearts as an identification symbol, according to the Ministry of
Health (MOH).
</P>
<P>
The symbol should be strategically placed in highly visible
locations in hospital buildings, according to an MOH circular
released today.
</P>
<P>
"The four red hearts symbolize love, patience, care and the
sense of responsibility of medical professionals. The symbol will
clearly designate a medical service center," according to the
circular.
</P>
<P>
Symbols for medical emergency centers and departments should be
illuminated at night, and can be painted on ambulances and other
hospital facilities.
</P>
<P>
Military hospitals which provide medical services to civilians
will to display the symbol, according to the circular, which was
jointly issued by the MOH and the Health Department of General
Logistics Department of the People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
The ministry introduced the new symbol in an attempt to halt
the illegal use of the internationally recognized Red Cross logo
displayed by some medical institutions which are not members of
the Red Cross Society, according to MOH official Li Dachuan.
</P>
<P>
The Law on the Red Cross Society and Methods Concerning the Use
of the Red Cross Symbol limits the use of the symbol to members of
the society.
</P>
<P>
"However, the fact that many medical institutions have simply
ignored the law and displayed the symbol has confused people,"
said Li.
</P>
<P>
"The unified use of the symbol is designed to make it more
convenient for people to locate medical care facilities,"
according to Li.
</P>
<P>
The ministry adopted a blue cross for medical institutions
early last year, but soon thereafter discontinued use of the
symbol which was registered by the veterinary sector.
</P>
<P>
A green cross currently serves as the unified symbol for the
nation's drug stores.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
