<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Share prices reversed their
downward trend and rose on the Singapore market on Thursday, as
the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index (STII) recovered
20.34 points to close at 1495.86 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the STII's gains were chiefly Keppel
Corporation, Cerebos Pacific and Singapore Press Holdings. Despite
the day's gains, they said this firmer tone might be sustainable
only over the next few days, testing the 1600-point level.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 156.17 million units,
valued at 278.72 million Singapore dollars (about 175.3 million
U.S. dollars). Advances overtook declined by 137 to 125, while 334
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Tai Sin was the most actively traded counter as it registered a
turnover of 29.45 million units. It was followed by Easyknit which
had 20.93 million shares traded. UniCorp was next with 7.68
million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local property developer City Developments led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 30 cents to finish at seven Singapore
dollars. Keppel Corporation increased by 24 cents to end at 4.42
Singapore dollars, while SIA (Singapore Airlines) Foreign and SPH
(Singapore Press Holdings) gained 20 cents each to close at 10.4
and 17.1 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, City Developments Warrant98 was the biggest
loser as it declined by 1.7 dollars to end at 3.6 Singapore
dollars. Creative 50 fell by 60 cents to close at 35.3 Singapore
dollars. Robinson was down by 26 cents to finish at 4.54 Singapore
dollars. 
</P>
