Lao Minister of Industries and Handicraft Soulivong Daravong
and Chinese Ambassador to Laos Zhao Jiahua signed a memorandum of
understanding on the hand-over of the plant.
</P>
<P>
Lao Deputy Prime Minister Boun-Nhang Vorachith took part in the
inauguration of the plant.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the plant was started in 1994 and finished in
March 1998 with a long-term loan of 59 million Renminbi Yuan
(about 7.12 million U.S. dollars) from China.
</P>
<P>
Equipped with three turbines capable of generating 500
kilowatts each, the plant has a 1,240-meter long canal and an
831-metre long tunnel from the reservoir to the power house.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
