<HEADLINE> Chinese, Zambian Foreign Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- China highly values its
traditional friendship with Zambia and is willing to work with that
country to bring the existing friendly, all-round cooperative
relations well into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan made the remarks today
in a meeting with his Zambian counterpart, Kelly Walubita, who is
on his first visit to China after taking office in December.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese and Zambian peoples have had traditional and
profound friendship, Tang said, adding that the Sino-Zambian
relation has remained good in the last 34 years since the
establishment of diplomatic relations although the global and
domestic situations have undergone remarkable changes.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, frequent high-level visits ensured the
development of cooperation in wide-ranging areas between the two
countries, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He said he is satisfied with the stable development of
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Tang said he appreciates the Zambian government's adherence to
the "one China" policy.
</P>
<P>
Walubita conveyed the greetings of Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba to Chinese President Jiang Zemin. He also extended his
appreciation for China's achievements in economic construction and
its positive role in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
He thanked China for its longtime support and help to Zambia,
and described China as an "all-weather" friend of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian foreign minister reiterated his country's
observation of the "one China" policy and recognition of the
government of the People's Republic of China as the sole legal
government of China, including Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Walubita arrived here Wednesday for a six-day official visit as
Tang's guest. He is expected to meet Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Besides Beijing, Walubita and his party will visit Nanchang,
capital of east China's Jiangxi Province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
