The first group of tours began earlier this month. There will
be many more in the summer and the program will be completed
before January 15, 1999, according to a spokesman for the
commission.
</P>
<P>
The commission has recently approved 82 applications for
sponsorship under the Community Participation Scheme for
Organizing Study Tours to inland areas. The total amount of
sponsorship is 6 million H.K. Dollars, equally funded between the
government and a local charities fund.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman for the commission said it has received more than
200 applications for fund to organize these study tours. The
total amount exceeded 30 million H.K. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
"This is very encouraging. It shows that many organizations are
keen to organize activities that are beneficial to the
development of youths," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that these study tours will help enhance local
youths' understanding of China. They will know more about Chinese
history and culture, and the political, economic, social system,
and the people's livelihood in China's inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Successful applicants are required to submit a report to the
commission after the tours.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
