<HEADLINE> Asia Pacific Leather Fair Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A 10-day-long Asia Pacific
Leather Fair which introduces new dimensions to the global leather
industry opened at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first of its kind held in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), attracting more than 4,300
companies from 65 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The fair, occupying a total exhibition space of 85,000 square
meters, stages two consecutive shows, one about the raw materials
and manufacturing show from April 23 to 26, and the other about
the spring show of fashion and finished products from April 30 to
May 2.
</P>
<P>
The two shows will present the most important innovators and
suppliers of leather manufacturing, technology and leather fashion
finished products in a new sectorized layout.
</P>
<P>
A total of 549 exhibitors from China are joining in the fair,
of which 417 are Hong Kong exhibitors.
</P>
<P>
Michael Duck, general manager of the Miller Freeman Asia Ltd.,
said at a press conference: "we are not just bringing to you a
bigger show. It is also important that we are holding the first
Asia Pacific Leather Fair in the new HKSAR of China after the
hand-over last July."
</P>
<P>
Though the entire region was affected in some way by the
economic and financial crisis last October, Hong Kong remains to
be the perfect regional venue for Asia Pacific Leather Fair, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said the international confidence in Hong Kong is evident
also by the recent remarks by the International Monetary Fund
which described Hong Kong as the "Pillar of Stability" in the
midst of the region's economic turmoil.
</P>
<P>
China's declaration of support to the HKSAR in many
international events further assures HK's continued success, he
added.
</P>
<P>
During the fair, a leather seminar on opportunities for
international companies in China's leather market is scheduled to
be held here on April 24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
