<HEADLINE> Malaysian Co. Takes Over Ugandan Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Westmont Land Berhad, a
Malaysian multinational company, took over Uganda Commercial Bank
(UCB) Thursday, the New Vision paper reported.
</P>
<P>
Westmont paid 11 million U.S. Dollars for Uganda's largest
bank.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Privatization Matthew Rukikaire and Enterprise
Development Project Executive Director Leonard Muganwa signed a
supplementary agreement with Westmont Wednesday to pave way for
the take-over of the bank's network of 74 branches in this east
African country.
</P>
<P>
Under the accord, Westmont will pay 429,842 U.S. Dollars as
interest for the extended deadline from October 27, 1997 when
both sides signed the main sale pact.
</P>
<P>
Muganwa said: "We have now signed an amendment to the sale
agreement that we signed last year with Westmont."
</P>
<P>
Westmont now holds 49 percent of the bank's shares and it can
buy more only after the Ugandan government share-holding has been
dropped to 25.5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
