<HEADLINE> More Cooperation Seen in UNCHR Session, Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The atmosphere of the current 54th
session of the United Nations Commission on Human Rights has been
of more cooperation and less confrontation than the previous
sessions, commission chairman Jacob Selebi said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
During the six-week session, commission members have been
trying to "seek a climate of cooperation and reduce
confrontation", Selebi said at a press conference before the
session ends on April 24.
</P>
<P>
He added that other features of the current session included
more emphasis on economic, social and cultural rights, and
agreement on the restructuring of the commission's mechanism by
consensus.
</P>
<P>
Selebi also noted that the commission had failed to resolve
some human rights violations in parts of the world. 
</P>
