<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Samsung Develops World's Lightest PCS Handset </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 23 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's Samsung electronic
company announced Thursday that it has successfully developed the
world's lightest PCS handset SPH-6310 with a weight of 77 grams,
including 18 grams of battery.
</P>
<P>
The SPH-6310, to be put on market next month, is loaded with
features such as voice recognition dialing, voice memos, rapid
Korean character input, instant dial, stopwatch, calculator and
100 number memory.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Samsung introduces lithium polymer battery into
the product, which is a fashionable bar type aimed at young buyers.
</P>
<P>
Samsung has developed two types of the lithium polymer battery,
which can be made into a variety of shapes to suit different
handset designs.
</P>
<P>
The low lithium polymer battery provides 30 minutes of call
time and eight hours on standby while the high-capacity one
supplies 240 minutes of call time and 80 hours on standby.
</P>
<P>
Samsung company, a subsidiary of South Korea-based Samsung
Group, is seen as one of the world's leaders in electronics, with
operation in more than 60 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
