<HEADLINE> Iranian Sheikh Murdered in Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, April 23 (Xinhua) -- An influential Iranian sheikh has
been murdered in Najaf, 170 Kilometers southwest of Baghdad by an
unidentified gunman, Iraq's Ministry of Awqaf and Religious
Affairs announced.
</P>
<P>
Ali Mohammad Ibrahem al-Brujerdi was shot to death Wednesday
night when he was heading for home after praying at the holy
shrine of Imam Ali, respected by Shiite Muslims as the first
successor of Prophet Mohammed.
</P>
<P>
Another two men accompanying him were injured, said the
announcement.
</P>
<P>
The murderer escaped from the scene, it said, stressing that
foreign intelligence was behind this crime "because of the
religious belief and moderate attitude" of the Iranian sheikh.
</P>
<P>
Al-Brujerdi, 70, is considered as one of the most famous
sheikhs in a religion academy in Najaf city, where the holy shrine
of Imam Ali is situated.
</P>
<P>
It is not immediately known whether this assassination will
impact Iraq's relations with neighboring Iran, where Shiite
Muslims are predominant.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi security officials are investigating this case and
searching for the murderer, said the announcement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
