<HEADLINE> Philippines to Launch Manila Segment of ASEAN Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines will formally
launch the Manila segment of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) Awards established by ASEAN leaders during their
Kuala Lumpur summit in December last year.
</P>
<P>
To be given every three years, the ASEAN Awards will publicly
recognize the outstanding work and contributions by both
individuals and institutions towards the promotion and development
of ASEAN regional cooperation, the Philippine Department of
Foreign Affairs said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN Awards aim to promote the region's objective of
"sharing prosperity through human development, technological
competitiveness and social cohesiveness," a statement from the
department said.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Foreign Affairs Secretary Domingo Siazon will
preside over the ASEAN Awards launching rites at the Cultural
Center of the Philippines on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The awards for individual accomplishments, it said, will
consist of a medal, a certificate and 10,000 U.S. dollars in cash.
While institutional winners will get a trophy, a certificate and a
100,000-dollar grant.
</P>
<P>
The cash portion of the prizes for institutional winners, it
said, will be intended to finance a research or related study to
be undertaken by the institution.
</P>
<P>
The final evaluation of ASEAN regional winners from among
national nominees will be made by an international panel of
judges, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
