<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Step up Renovation of State-run Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van
Khai issued an order to accelerate the renovation of state-run
businesses on april 21, local press reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In a bid to improve the national economic situation, Khai asked
government offices and state-run corporations to restructure,
strengthen and reorganize various state businesses. At
present, only 30 percent of them are making profit.
</P>
<P>
Khai said, "Those which are profitable will be given favourable
conditions for further growth. Those that experienced funding
difficulties will be given more finance."
</P>
<P>
In recent year, the Vietnamese government has produced a number
of policies and regulations to improve state-run businesses and
enhance their operation efficiency.
</P>
<P>
However, signs of slowdown could still be seen in state-run
businesses which stop them from achieving their main economic
targets. 
</P>
