<HEADLINE> China To Present Outstanding Achievement Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Some 1,000 model workers and 300
advanced work units from across the nation will receive top honors
for their achievements.
</P>
<P>
The workers will receive "May 1st" labor medals from the
All-China Federation of Trade Unions (ACFTU), with advanced units
receiving "May 1st" certificates of merit. Ten workers will be
listed as the "Top Ten Outstanding Workers".
</P>
<P>
Some 54 percent of the 1,000 outstanding workers hold
grass-roots positions. Scientists, researchers and technicians
account for 15.4 percent of the total, with factory leaders and
company managers accounting for 9.4 percent of the honorees. The
list also includes 172 women and 54 members of ethnic minorities.
</P>
<P>
ACFTU Vice-chairperson Ni Haomei said here today that this
year's awards focus on excellent workers, scientists, researchers
and technicians who have made great contribution to science and
technology, national defence and major construction projects.
</P>
<P>
The list of the top 10 outstanding workers includes people from
the automobile manufacturing, mining and iron industry, as well as
from railway bureau and posts and telecommunications
departments. The winners come from ten provinces, autonomous
regions and municipalities.
</P>
<P>
Four of the 10 workers, between the ages of 36 and 56, have
made great contribution to technological renovations, with six
doing difficult, strenuous, dangerous or dirty jobs, according to
Ni.  
</P>
</TEXT>
