<HEADLINE> Chemical Sector Records Monthly Production Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The total first quarter
production value for China's chemical industry reached 65.08
billion yuan, up 1.8 percent on the 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the State Administration of Petroleum
and Chemical Industry show the sector achieved monthly production
growth during the quarter.
</P>
<P>
The total production value of the chemical industry for March
stood at 25.42 billion yuan, up 13.6 percent on February, with the
figure for the latter month growing by 12.6 percent on January.
</P>
<P>
March production increases were recorded for 12 of 16
chemical-based products, including fertilizers, sulphuric acid,
pesticides and tires.
</P>
<P>
China produced 2.3 million tons of fertilizers during March,
with the first quarter total standing at 6.12 million tons.
</P>
<P>
March pesticide production stood at 38,000 tons, with the
quarterly figure standing at 93,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The statistics also indicated improvements in the
interrelationship between the industry's production and sales,
with the March sales-production ratio standing at 96.3
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
