<HEADLINE> Zambian to Reduce Int'l Telecom Tariffs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- From the May 1 those who make
international communication calls will enjoy 30 percent reduction
of tariffs in Zambia, Zambia Telecommunication Company said.
</P>
<P>
In a nation-wide announcement available here Thursday, the
company said that to improve and expand telecommunication
services, it has decided to reduce the international
telecommunication service charges to the lowest ever levels.
</P>
<P>
In addition, customers will get another reduction of 25 percent
during off peak hours.
</P>
<P>
According to the announcement, the charge to the member
countries of the Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa
(COMESA) will be reduced to 1.8 U.S. Dollars from 2.8 Dollars a
minute and 1.4 Dollars a minute at off peak hours while the
charge for Europe, the U.S. and India reduced to 2.2 Dollars from
3.2 Dollars and 1.6 Dollars will be for off peak hours per
minute.
</P>
<P>
Off peak hours include 18:00 to 07:00 from Monday to Friday as
well as public holidays. 
</P>
