<HEADLINE> Kuwait to Further Improve Quality of Fuel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait Minister of Oil
Sheikh Saud Nasser Al-Sabah has said that Kuwait is managing to
further reduce lead contend in petrol to improve the quality
of fuel in the local market.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by Kuwait's English daily Arab Times as saying
Thursday that Kuwait's National Petroleum Company has planned to
reduce the lead content in petrol in the local market to the
minimum possible level.
</P>
<P>
He did not specify it further, but he pointed that the lead
content in "Octane 90" and "Octane 98", the fuel available in
Kuwait market had been separately reduced to 0.53 and 0.3 gram per
litre since 1996.
</P>
<P>
The minister also disclosed that his country, one of the
dominant oil producers in the world, had further plans to reduce
the sulphur content in diesel to 0,25 percent starting next year.
</P>
<P>
Sulphur content in diesel had been reduced from one percent to
the current 0.5 percent since July 1996, the oil minister said.
</P>
</TEXT>
