<HEADLINE> Mugabe Blasts WCC for Backing Homos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert
Mugabe has Blasted organizers of the World Council of Churches
(WCC) for allowing gays and lesbians to participate in their
conference to be held in Harare from December 3 to 14.
</P>
<P>
In a charged speech during the funeral of the late Herald
Editor Charles Chikerema, President Mugabe said animals in the
jungle were better than gays and lesbians, "because at least they
know that this is a man or a woman."
</P>
<P>
Mugabe said that homosexualism was not part of Zimbabwean
culture and was not Christianity either, the Zimbabwe News Agency
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The president also castigated the independent media for
playing in the white's hands.
</P>
<P>
"In Britain, you will never find a paper that speaks badly
against that country. Why then in Zimbabwe do we not adopt a
common ideology," said Mugabe.
</P>
<P>
He praised Chikerema for having worked diligently over the
years in supporting the ideology of the Zimbabwean government.
Chikerema died on Tuesday afternoon at the age of 59. 
</P>
