<HEADLINE> Cholera Outbreak in Southern Philippines Contained </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The cholera outbreak in at least
four hinterland villages in North Upi, the southern province of
Maguindanao, is now under control, the provincial health office
declared Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Tahir Sulaik, Maguindanao health officer, said so far, there
were no more reported additional deaths, particularly on the part
of the Tiruray tribespeople, after emergency relief and medical
assistance were sent to the area.
</P>
<P>
"The last case of cholera we received was at noon of April 21,
last Tuesday," Sulaik noted.
</P>
<P>
The outbreak, which was reported only late last week, claimed
at least eight lives, mostly children, in the villages of Nalkan,
Tambak, Penansaran and Tubuan.
</P>
<P>
A total of 104 cholera cases were recorded by health
authorities in North Upi, Sulaik said.
</P>
<P>
Sulaik said medical teams will continue with their work in the
affected villages to monitor further the possible recurrence of
the disease. 
</P>
