<HEADLINE> China Sets up Insurance Examination Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A Charted Property Casualty
Underwriter Examination Center, the first of its kind in China,
will be set up in east China's Shanghai Municipality.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Chubb Group of Insurance Companies of the
United States and the Shanghai University of Economics and
Finance, the center will provide classes and examinations for
insurance practitioners in pursuing industry standards.
</P>
<P>
Examinations will be held twice a year, in January and June.
</P>
<P>
To qualify for the examination, all candidates need to have at
least three years of experience in insurance with an average of
17.5 working hours or more each week. They also must pass nine
national examinations.
</P>
<P>
The first examinations will be conducted in May of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The Chubb Group is pleased to help establish industry standards
in China and will provide all necessary support to make sure the
classes and exams are carried out smoothly, said a high-ranking
official with the company.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1882, the Chubb Group is one of the largest
insurance companies in the world and is also the first foreign
insurance company to establish Greater China headquarters in
Beijing. It has representative offices in Beijing, Shanghai and
Shenzhen.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
