<DOCNO> XIE19980423.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Calls For Closer Sino-Japanese Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao said here Thursday that his current visit is aimed at
bringing a closer Sino-Japanese relationship forward into the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a reception hosted in his honor by seven Japanese
organizations for promoting Japan-China friendship, Hu said that
the normalization of Sino-Japanese relations 26 years ago and the
Sino-Japanese Peace and Friendship Treaty signed 20 years ago have
laid a solid foundation for the two nations to maintain and
advance friendship.
</P>
<P>
Hu said for many years the two countries and their peoples have
worked hard to promote cooperation in economy, trade, science and
technology and culture and have scored marked achievements.
</P>
<P>
He said that both China and Japan as important countries in
Asia and the world should consider in real earnest the question of
developing their good-neighborly ties so as to build lasting
friendship.
</P>
<P>
Hu said the Chinese people, once subject to grave humiliation
by foreign aggressors, cherish very much their hard-won national
independence.
</P>
<P>
China has made remarkable progress in various fields since it
adopted the policy of reform and opening-up 20 years ago.
However, Hu said, China has still to battle a hard battle to
achieve comprehensive modernization.
</P>
<P>
Hu said China will continue to follow the path designated by
the late leader Deng Xiaoping and endeavor to push forward its
drive of reform, opening-up and modernization.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of China's independent foreign policy of peace, Hu
said that China will continue to build and develop friendly and
cooperative ties with all other nations on the basis of Five
Principles of Peaceful Co-Existence, and strive for a peaceful and
stable international environment, particularly a favorable
environment.
</P>
<P>
Hu stressed that China will never seek hegemonism even after it
becomes a developed nation in the future. He said China will
always stand as a strong force in maintaining regional and global
peace and stability, a solemn commitment of the Chinese
people to the world.
</P>
<P>
Japan opted for the road of peaceful development after the end
of World War II, and its international status has obviously
improved with remarkable economic achievements, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China hopes Japan would learn lessons from
history, continue to be on the road of peaceful development and
play a more positive role in promoting international economic
cooperation and maintaining world peace.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Japanese relations constitute an important part of the
present international relations, Hu noted. As two important
members of the international community, China and Japan shoulder
great responsibility for strengthening international cooperation,
promoting joint development, maintaining peace and stability in
Asia and the world as a whole, and pushing for the establishment
of a just and rational international political and economic order,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The state of Sino-Japanese relations in the 21st century will
have impact not only on the fundamental interests of the two
countries and their peoples, but also on the healthy development
of the overall international relations, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Communist Party and the Chinese government have
always been handling Sino-Japanese ties from a realistic,
long-term point of view, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
China and Japan should adhere to the principles and spirit set
in the Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and Sino-Japanese Peace and
Friendship Treaty, boost dialogue, deepen mutual understanding,
respect each other and not interfere in each other's internal
affairs, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
He also said the two countries should seek more common ground
while reserving differences, handle differences properly, promote
mutually beneficial economic cooperation and establish lasting
friendly ties for the future.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that Sino-Japanese relationship should become an
example of good-neighborliness for countries with different social
and political systems.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries should be partners of
development on the basis of equality and mutual benefits in
economy, be friends who learn from each other in culture, science
and technology, and be positive forces which maintain world peace
and promote common development of the world.
</P>
<P>
Hu expressed his belief that Sino-Japanese ties will have a
better future in the next century as more and more of the
younger generation in the two countries will devote themselves to
promoting friendly bilateral relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
