<DOCNO> XIE19980423.0220 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FAO Regional Ministerial Meeting Starts in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A two-day ministerial meeting of
the 24th Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) Regional
Conference for Asia and the Pacific commenced here Thursday
following a three-day senior officials meeting.
</P>
<P>
The ministerial meeting is scheduled to further discuss food
security, follow-ups to the World Food Summit, and management and
conservation of fisheries resources.
</P>
<P>
First Secretary of Myanmar State Peace and development Council
lieutenant-general Khin Nyunt made an inaugural speech at the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
He said that the conference will be a success and able to
provide meaningful inputs to the food security of not only this
region but also the world.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Myanmar and many other countries in the region
need a favorable economic environment.
</P>
<P>
He said for developing countries, a favorable economic
environment would mean a respite from the external debt burden and
debts overhung, remunerative prices for their agricultural
products, greater investment and aid to the agricultural sector,
enhanced assistance from organizations like the FAO in fishery,
forestry and agriculture, greater cooperation between the
countries of the region and the agencies and organizations of the
United Nations and the FAO.
</P>
<P>
The just-ended senior officials meeting of the conference
called for urgent actions to promote fisheries and sustainable
development of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Participants agreed that greater attention should be paid to
fisheries management and international cooperation and
coordination strengthened in fisheries conservation and management
in the region.
</P>
<P>
The conference, the first regional gathering of agricultural
ministers since the 1996 World Food Summit in Rome, Italy, is
being attended by about 150 representatives from 25 FAO member
countries in Asia and the Pacific, non-governmental organizations
and U.N. agencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
