<HEADLINE> Hu: Trade, Important Pillar in Sino-Japanese Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 23 (Xinhua)-- Bilateral trade ties are an
important pillar for enhancing Sino-Japanese friendly relations,
visiting Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Hu made this remark during a meeting with Yoshio Sakurauchi,
President of Japan's Association for International Trade Promotion.
</P>
<P>
Hu said the Japanese organization has made great contributions
to the Sino-Japanese friendship and the expansion of bilateral
trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Sakurauchi told Hu that his organization would continue its
efforts to expand cooperation with China, especially in such
fields as energy and environmental protection, which have great
potentials.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with representatives of Japan's youth
organizations, Hu said that the Sino-Japanese relations are now in
a period of inheriting the past and ushering in the futures.
</P>
<P>
It is a common task for the governments and politicians of the
two countries to bring the friendly ties into the next century, Hu
said, adding that young people of both countries also shoulder the
great responsibility of advancing bilateral relationship.
</P>
<P>
The representatives told Hu they appreciate his willingness to
boost exchanges between young people of Japan and China, and said
they believe that the long-term, stable bilateral friendly ties
will be brought into the 21st century under the joint efforts of
young people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice president, who is here on a six-day official
visit, attended a breakfast hosted in his honor by Japan's
Federation of Economic Organizations (Keidanren) earlier in the
day. 
</P>
