<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government is worried
about the continued decline in agriculture, a critical factor to
this east African country's industrialization process, the East
African Standard reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture Minister Musalia Mudavadi Wednesday cited a slump
in coffee and tea production as further proof that the situation
needs immediate attention.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture's growth played a major role if Kenya is to
industrialize, he said, calling for urgent remedial measures to
reverse the trend.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan government should act fast and put agricultural
sector on a faster growth path, said the minister.
</P>
