should be realized to trigger off the industrialization," he
noted.
</P>
<P>
"We should revamp virtually all the agricultural sub-sectors
such as coffee, cereal, dairy, cotton, pyrethrum, tea, sugar
cane, horticultural exports and others which have recorded a
decreased output in the recent past," he said.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture makes up directly approximately 25 percent of the
gross domestic product in Kenya which has targeted to have itself
industrialized before 2020. 
