<HEADLINE> Colombia and Chile Tie 2-2 in World Cup Warmup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, April 22 (Xionhua) -- Chile and Colombia played to a
2-2 draw in their World Cup soccer tuneup match here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Javier Margas headed home to open the account for Chile in the
21st minute.
</P>
<P>
After a fruitless 68 minutes, Leider Preciado equalized for the
visitors. Two minutes later he put Colombia ahead.
</P>
<P>
The lead was short-lived, however, as Marcelo Salas, who
miss-fired a penalty attempt in the 76th minute, responded in the
84th to give Chile the draw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
