<HEADLINE> Virus Flu Hits Sri Lanka Hard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A virus flu has hit Sri Lanka
hard and the country's hospitals are overflowing with patients
suffering from it, according to Medical research Institute (MRI)
sources here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The number of patients at the Colombo National Hospital and Sri
Jayawardenapura Hospital in Colombo has increased from 200 to 700
every day. Many area hospitals in the country are full of patients
and 17 children have died in the past few days, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The virus has affected both adults and children alike.
</P>
<P>
However, the medical authorities have been unable to identify
the virus. The MRI has started investigations into the epidemic
and will try to find out how this virus spreads, according to the
sources.
</P>
<P>
Some doctors are of the opinion that the virus may be a
combination of two or more varieties.
</P>
<P>
According to hospital sources, the symptoms of the virus flu
are high fever, cough, vomiting, stomachache and liver problems.
</P>
<P>
However, some doctors believe that the virus is actually a
common influenza but people seek medical treatment fearing it is
deadly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
