<HEADLINE> Brunel Sunergy Wins Whitbread Seventh Leg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Netherlands' Brunel Sunergy,
skippered by Roy Heiner, swept to victory on Wednesday in the
seventh leg of the Whitbread Round the World Race.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Baltimore, Maryland, the Dutch Boat
crossed the finishing line in Baltimore at 16:59:39 local time
(20:59:39 GMT).
</P>
<P>
The Dutchman and his crew kept the pressure on all the way to
the finishing line, with their two closest rivals, Swedish Match
and EF Language, in sight behind.
</P>
<P>
Swedish Match, skippered by Gunnar Krantz and Erle Williams,
just slipped home ahead of Paul Cayard's EF Language, while Conner
beat Collins by a mere 10 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The seventh of the nine legs in the Whitbread race was a
870-mile sprint from Florida's Fort Lauderdale to Baltimore in
Maryland, 100 miles up Chesapeake Bay from the Atlantic Ocean.
</P>
