<HEADLINE> Export-oriented Agriculture Successful in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Nantong, a coastal city in east
China's Jiangsu Province, earned more than 1.2 billion US dollars
from exporting agricultural and side-line produce in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The province's success should be attributed to rapid progress
in the city's comprehensive development of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the city established a group of production
centers for cotton and vegetables, raising lean-type pigs and
developing aquatic products, which are exported to almost 100
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Farmers in the city have also made a greater effort to improve
low- and medium-yielding fields as well as growing vegetables and
trees.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, they have made full use of tidal flats and developed
10 export-oriented producing centers which are engaged in
producing organic food products.
</P>
<P>
To increase exports of farm produce, the city has attracted
funds from the Netherland, Japan and the Taiwan region. 
