<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Every 100 Czechs Have 32 Telephones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Czech Republic is reported to
have the largest number of telephones per capita in Central and
East European countries.
</P>
<P>
Statistics of the Telecommunications Bureau showed there were
3.37 million telephones in the country by the end of 1997, or 31.7
telephones for every 100 people. Hungary came second with 28.6,
followed by Slovak and Poland.
</P>
<P>
According to the bureau, by the year 2000, every 100 Czechs
will have 44.8 telephones and over 90 percent of the telephones
will be program-controlled.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, mobile phones had numbered 700,000 by the end of
March, doubling the figure at the end of last year. The number of
mobile phones is expected to rise to 1.1 million by 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
