<HEADLINE> Return of Cambodians in Thailand to Be Discussed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Thailand, Cambodia and the U. N.
High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) will discuss here on Monday
the repatriation of some 64,000 Cambodians in Thailand before
Cambodia's July 26 elections, according to the Thai Foreign
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The meeting follows a call by the ASEAN troika on the Cambodian
government to "facilitate" the safe return of displaced
Cambodians, and on the UNHCR to provide assistance so that the
Cambodians are back in their homeland "in time to participate in
the election process."
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) troika
comprises three ASEAN members -- Indonesia, the Philippines and
Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Thai Deputy Foreign Minister Sukhumbhand Paribatra was quoted
Thursday by the Bangkok Post as saying the operation would be
carried out on a strictly voluntary basis, with no force employed
in the process.
</P>
<P>
According to Sukhumbhand, the UNHCR has promised to extend the
utmost support to the repatriation.
</P>
<P>
Sukhumbhand said he would lead the Thai delegation to the
meeting. his Cambodian counterpart, Uch Kim-An, and a UNHCR
representative would be the other co-chairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
