<HEADLINE> Belgrade Smokers Eligible For Anti-Smoking Contest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Smokers in Belgrade can enter an
anti-smoking contest in May jointly sponsored by 50 nations, a
Belgrade Public Health Bureau statement said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the contest, which is scheduled for May
2-29, will provide contenders with an opportunity to challenge
themselves to give up smoking and enjoy the sweet taste of victory.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, smokers who are 18 years of age or
older and have been smoking for at least one year are eligible to
participate.
</P>
<P>
In addition, participants have to submit a formal report from a
hospital on the nicotine content of their blood when they come to
register in the Public Health Bureau before May 2.
</P>
<P>
At the end of May, the public health authorities are expected
to select the winners, who will join winners from other countries
in a lottery totaling 100,000 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
