<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Encouraged In Water-Resource Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- China is open to foreign
participation in its water-resource development, and area of
promising benefits for both parties, Zhu Dengquan of the Ministry
Water Resources (MWR) said here today.
</P>
<P>
The vice-minister said that China's rapid economic growth needs
an adequate water supply, hydro-power generation and flood
prevention, However, funding and technology constraints have
impeded progress in developing the country's water resources.
</P>
<P>
China used 480 million U.S. dollars of direct overseas
investment in the water resources sector during the 1992-1996
period, accounting for 0.3 percent of the total overseas
investment figure in China, according to statistics provided by
the International Cooperation Department of the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Zhu told Xinhua that China is improving investment conditions
for overseas businesses, with major changes planned in the
bureaucratic system and legal construction this year.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the newly elected cabinet, the State
Council, is working to achieve unified management over water
resources, to strengthen the ministry's ability to manage water
affairs.
</P>
<P>
That means, he explained, that overseas businesses may no
longer need to go through the current web of government
departments to have a project approved, but will only need one
approval -- that of the MWR.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
