<HEADLINE> Demonstration Against Child Labor Continues March to Honduras </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A global demonstration targeting
against child labor left Nicaragua Wednesday for Honduras and will
continue on to Central America and Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The Latin American demonstration, which began in Brazil in
February and arrived here on Sunday, is aimed at organizing a
large number of people to join the fight against the exploitation
of child labor.
</P>
<P>
Nicaraguan Minister of Labor Wilfredo Navarro said his country
is willing to start national programs to eliminate child labor.
</P>
<P>
According to the program, the demonstration representatives
will enter the southern border of Mexico on May 1, which will end
their trip through Central America, the Dominican Republic and
Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the worldwide protest is also being held in Asia and
Africa.
</P>
<P>
In the first week of June, the demonstrators will arrive in
Geneva, Switzerland, their final destination, where leaders of
many countries will hold a meeting to determine measures to be
taken to end the exploitation of children as a form of cheap
labor. 
