 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Speaking at a national conference for
demobilized soldiers, President Jiang Zemin said in Beijing
yesterday that local governments should provide jobs for
demobilized soldiers and help them receive proper job training.
</P>
<P>
This year, some 50,000 officers of the People's Liberation Army
and the armed police will be transferred to civilian work and the
number will grow in 1999 and 2000. This is in accordance with the
country's announcement last October to cut its armed forces by
500,000 by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
