<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Port Has Three More Wharfs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Three newly built wharfs in
Fuzhou, capital of east China's Fujian Province, have been opened
for service. The wharfs have a combined annual handling capacity
of 1.28 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Fuzhou now is one of the two pilot ports approved by the
Ministry of Communications to exchange direct navigation services
with Taiwan. It has 46 productive wharfs and 11 deep-water berths.
</P>
<P>
The three wharfs, located at the mouth of Minjiang River,
include the Guantou Wharf specialized in Taiwan-related services;
the Choudonghe Sand Wharf; and the Ji'an Oil Wharf. Chinese ships
on international routes and overseas ships can dock at the
wharfs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
