<HEADLINE> Greece Backs Hungary in NATO, EU Applications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Greek President Costis
Stephanopoulos on Wednesday voiced his support for Hungary in its
bid to join the North Atlantic Treaty Organization and the
European Union.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with his Hungarian counterpart Arpad Goncz here,
Stephanopoulos said the Greek parliament will ratify NATO's
eastward expansion protocol soon.
</P>
<P>
The Greek president urged the EU to step up its negotiation
process to enable Hungary to join it as soon as possible. He said
the Western European Union should also be expanded.
</P>
<P>
Stephanopoulos and Goncz agreed that there were no disputes
between Greece and Hungary and they urged the two countries to tap
the potential of economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Last July, NATO leaders decided to accept Poland, Hungary and
the Czech Republic by 1999. The decision needs to be approved by
the parliaments of member countries. 
