<HEADLINE> Pudong Attracting Funds From All Over China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- At the Pudong New Area in
Shanghai, 4,569 projects were built with investments from other
parts of China in the last eight years, according to a local
official.
</P>
<P>
More than 90 -- nearly half of the high-rise buildings in
Pudong -- were built by central government ministries and
commissions or governments of other provinces.
</P>
<P>
East China's Jiangsu Province was the largest domestic investor
in Pudong with an investment exceeding one billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The former Ministry of Electronic Industry cooperated with
Japan-based Nippon Electric Co. Ltd. to build a
one-billion-U.S. dollar electronic joint venture in the Jinqiao
export-oriented processing zone, becoming the largest project in
Pudong invested by government ministries.
</P>
<P>
The 421-meter-high Jinmao Mansion, the highest skyscraper so
far built in China, was jointly funded by 14 foreign trade
companies under the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Nearly half of the 89 sub-trade companies opened in Pudong by
25 provinces and cities were set up by provinces along the Yangtze
River belt.
</P>
<P>
The Pufa Machine-Building Industry Co. Ltd., a group of 200
enterprises, was rated the most profitable firm set up by
government ministries. Its assets quadrupled in four years.
</P>
</TEXT>
