<HEADLINE> Cuba Hails Defeat of Anti-Cuban Resolution in U.N. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Cuba has hailed as "victorious"
the defeat of an anti-Cuban resolution presented by the United
States in the Human Rights Commission of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
In an editorial published Wednesday, the official Granma
journal said that April 21, Tuesday, was a "historical day" when
the anti-Cuban resolution was defeated with 19 votes against, 16
for and 18 abstentions in Geneva, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
What happened in Geneva Tuesday dismantled the mechanism used
by Washington to charge Cuba with human rights violations, the
journal said.
</P>
<P>
With this outcome, a great stride was made in destroying the
U.S. mechanisms of aggression, manipulation and negative publicity
against Cuba, it said.
</P>
<P>
Cuba is prepared to conduct dialogues on the basis of mutual
respect, the journal said. But it stressed that by no means will
Cuba accept an imposition of any pretended values against Cuban
socialism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
