<HEADLINE> Soybean Production to Set New Record in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Soybean production in
Brazil will set a new record this year reaching more than 30
million tons, the local press reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report disclosed that with soybean cultivation areas
increasing from 11 million hectares last year to 13 million
hectares this year, soybean production will reach 30.93 million
tons this year compared to 26.16 million tons last year,
establishing a new historical record.
</P>
<P>
However, due to the fall of soybean prices in the international
market, Brazil is expected to earn 5 to 5.3 billion U.S. dollars
from the export of soybeans this year.
</P>
<P>
This amount represents a slight reduction if compared with that
of last year, when the country registered an income from soybeans
of more than 5.7 billion dollars. 
</P>
