<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Newspapers Focus More on Environmental Protection, Survey Shows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese newspapers are paying
more attention to environmental protection issues, the latest
survey on the media shows.
</P>
<P>
The survey included 76 newspapers which published 22,066
stories concerning environmental protection in 1997, a monthly
average of 24 stories for each compared with 21 in 1996 and 11 in
1995.
</P>
<P>
Only Science and Technology Daily and Legal Daily's reports on
environmental protection exceeded 1 percent of their total
coverage in 1995. But in 1997 some 48 newspapers exceeded the
percentage.
</P>
<P>
Except those special environmental media, Science and
Technology Daily was most concerned about environmental protection
in 1997, the survey says.
</P>
<P>
Newspapers from coastal areas also showed more enthusiasm about
environmental issues.
</P>
<P>
The newspapers attached the greatest importance to planting
trees, public hygiene and governmental response to environmental
problems, the survey shows.  
</P>
